{"talk":{"id":2590,"name":"Helen Fisher: Technology hasn't changed love. Here's why","description":"In our tech-driven, interconnected world, we've developed new ways and rules to court each other, but the fundamental principles of love have stayed the same, says anthropologist Helen Fisher. Our faster connections, she suggests, are actually leading to slower, more intimate relationships. At 12:20, couples therapist and relationship expert Esther Perel steps in to make an important point -- that while love itself stays the same, technology has affected the way we form and end relationships.","slug":"helen_fisher_technology_hasn_t_changed_love_here_s_why","recorded_at":"2016-06-27 00:00:00","published_at":"2016-09-30 15:03:27","updated_at":"2020-09-28 21:45:26","viewed_count":1918675,"emailed_count":0,"event":{"id":424,"name":"TEDSummit"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a61bce8bee0740137fbd4ae8c3628443db8806db_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a61bce8bee0740137fbd4ae8c3628443db8806db_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a61bce8bee0740137fbd4ae8c3628443db8806db_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"2400x1800","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a61bce8bee0740137fbd4ae8c3628443db8806db_2400x1800.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/258c5275b201c958dcd88d088ef3205f9b82c20c_2880x1620.jpg","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/HelenFisher_2016T-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":9423281,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/HelenFisher_2016T-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":26137290,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/HelenFisher_2016T-320k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":